      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Antinice</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> At 37 the druids are prime targets, as are the guards in the same zone.  But you do have to be careful.  Make sure your pet is always Augmented.  Fear one druid.  It will run back and forth stupidly, right at the druid ring.  Then either:</P><P>1) "If they are Feared they can't hurt you" approach: Send pet after the other.  Fear this druid too.  Keep the druids feared :-D.  DD or Tap as appropriate.</P><P>2) "I can handle one-at-a-time" approach: While one is Feared, pull the other to the tree S of the rings.  Then snare and fear it too.  You can pull it with a snare but make sure you pull it far enough from the 1st druid.  You might have to hammer the "pet back off" key.  When you have the two druids separated, ST the first druid, then Feign.  If you have the situation under control, Feign again.  The idea, obvously, is to clear the aggro so you don't have to fight both mobs at the same time.  When doing this sort of thing, ALWAYS keep an eye on the first mob.  You don't want to be blindsided.  I prefer this approach to the former.</P><P>3) Ask a high level to nuke a druid for you.  There, they're split.</P><P>I quit dotting these mobs, they are too flimsy. I changed to Tap and DD.</P><P>If your initial Fear is resisted, back the pet off and Feign.  This may not work since if they cast on you while you're casting Feign it will not work, but you have to try something.  Or, send the pet in and run for Befallen while they eat your pet.  It's only 2 bonechips :-D</P><P>Buy SOW potions.</P><P>When you hit 39 this camp gets simple - and fun.  You'll be amazed how your extra spells allow you to own this camp.  It's good to 44 or so.</P><P></P><P>Antinice, 47th Necro, Torvus`Vir, Druzzil Ro<BR>Nothing says, "I Hate You" like a DoT</P><P>Edited by - Antinice on 09/02/2002  00:55:19</font></td>
