        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>timdini</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Alright here is the secret.  </P><P>But first my background.  I did 34 to 36 in Dawnshroud.  Great xp but no loot (well some fungi covered mushrooms, but they were uncommon drops!) Sooooo where to go?  At 36 I decided to try the Druids in EC.  It's quiet there, no one EVER challenged my camp.  I only died once in the beginning until I learned THE SECRET.</P><P>So here is how to split them AND stay alive.  This really is a NO FAIL method!</P><P>Screaming Terror.  Yup thats about it.  The problem: What if ST resists?  Here is the answer: Gate.</P><P>So you walk up to the spawn, Screaming Terror one TWO things can happen:<BR>1. The Spell takes hold, one Druid/Ranger runs at you.  You sick pet on it, Darken it, Fear it, Tap to get life back from CoB or AoD.  When it dies, med for 3 minutes.  Pull other ST'd Druid/Ranger.</P><P>2. Screaming Terror RESISTS.  Gate, lose your pet, rezone into EC and try again.  Gate again if it resists.  TRUST ME it is NOT worth it to try and take 2 at a time (although it is possible with Invoke Fear!)  It will drain your mana and that is bad since you won't have enough to kill the next pops and its very possible they will both pop within a mintue of each other.</P><P>So once I had it split I held the camp until I was encumbered with Plat.  (I am a Gnome and could sell to the Huts nearby.)  I could make about 150-200 plat an hour.  I made a TON of plat here and upgraded all my gear to what it is now pretty much on the plat that I earned by these Druids.  I went all the way up to 39 off of them.  And YES at 37 you easily have enough mana to take them.  Occasionally you WILL have to heal your pet...okay okay A LOT, but use mend bones and its not so bad.  You WILL appreciate your level 39 pet when you get it, it regens INSANELY fast compared to the 34 one.</P><P>Good luck to you all and DON'T be afraid of this camp!  Its is mind numbingly easy.</P><P></P><P><strong>Deedrok - Level 41<BR>  Necromancer of E'ci<BR>  <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=234678" target="_blank">My Gear</a></strong></P><P>Edited by - timdini on 09/05/2002  08:24:01</font></td>
