        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Dravenlee</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Ok.  This is how I did both the EC and WC druids.  First, EC:  Fear one and while the spell is casting, keep clicking on other.  When second druid is tageted (assuming the first ran like a bat out of Hades!!!), Darkness, Fear, Pet, DOT, and wait for death, renewing spells as needed.  When druid dies, med and wait for other to return.  Follow same stratagy, but pace yourself to allow for time between spawns.  Once both are dead, loot, med, and hit the next spawn AS SOON AS THEY RESPAWN!!!  This way they don't buff themselves.  As for the WC druids, don't bother ST or any of that.  MY advice is to send pet in to attack one, and fear the other.  Fear the one your pet is on, and keep fear on BOTH of them.  Don't worry about Darkness, b/c at the rings, there is a pathing error that makes them run within a certain area of the rings, back and forth.  Pet will have no trouble keeping up with them.  Dot, blast, med, whatever your favorite choice of fighting is, but make sure you keep fear up!!!  There is a real danger here if fear wears off and one druid starts healing the other.  Just use FD and wait for pet to die and for druids to go back to spawn point.  When you kill first, pace yourself on the second for same reason as the EC druids, and have fun!!!  I can make about 100pp an hour in either spot, and make a good bit of xp.  Hope this helps you guys!  Happy hunting and Godspeed!</P><P><BR>Dravenlee O'Barr<BR>Necromancer of the 43rd lv of Knowledge<BR>Fennin Ro<BR>"My dreams are a reality that I can't hold on to, and reality is a dream that refuses to let me go."</P><P> </font></td>
