        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> hmmm, maybe they changed ST then?  I camped the Rangers (at least, I think they were Rangers.  They droped ringmail, bows, and swords) in WC for several levels.  If I had to solo them, I would park my pet way over by the lake, then ST one and run back to my pet.  This way I ended up fighting on the far side of the little hill from the ST'd Ranger.  Even so, sometimes he would come charging in once ST wore off.</P><P>If the second did charge in (either through a resist or by it's memory not being wiped), I would gate to EC and start over...the mirror image of what Timdini was doing in EC.</P><P>I liked the WC treehuggers better because of the merchant right there.  I believe the Dr00d ring merchants are on beta neutral faction?  I know I can still buy and sell from them with every toon I have.</P><P>I couldn't effectively solo them until 39th.  Even then it was tough.  If I got unlucky with resists I would fall too far behind in mana and have to re-break.  I usually looked for a partner.</P><P>-Falstep</P><P> </font></td>
